{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"270eeaa0-707d-44a9-b37e-846c881f6ebe","content":"Run **`dotnet workload update`**.\n\nAfter a .NET SDK update, your installed workloads (like `maui`) may be pinned to versions compatible with the *old* SDK. `dotnet workload update` downloads and installs the **latest versions** of all installed workloads, matching them to your current SDK.\n\n`dotnet workload repair` only **reinstalls** the currently-installed versions — it fixes corrupted installs but won't pull newer, SDK-compatible versions. So it likely won't resolve your build break.\n\n**Quick fix:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload update\ndotnet build   # verify the build works again\n```\n\nIf you still see issues afterward, check `dotnet workload list` to confirm the `maui` workload is present and up to date.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8c9b5e31-d1e5-45eb-8d2b-94ff8c0eb4fc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI workload management — specifically whether to use `dotnet workload update` or `dotnet workload repair` after a .NET SDK update broke their build.\n\nThis is a general knowledge question, not tied to any code in the working directory. I can answer directly.\n\n**`dotnet workload update`** — Downloads and installs the latest versions of all installed workloads. This is what you want after an SDK update, because the workload versions need to match the new SDK.\n\n**`dotnet workload repair`** — Reinstalls all installed workloads to fix corrupted installations. It doesn't update them to newer versions; it just re-downloads and reinstalls the current versions.\n\n\nThe right move here is `dotnet workload update` — after upgrading the SDK, you need workloads that align with the new version, and that's exactly what `update` does. Using `repair` would just reinstall the old versions, which might not be compatible with your new SDK.","outputTokens":422,"requestId":"F404:2EB5E6:1F5C642:232647E:69E81998"},"id":"919f9b2c-73ea-4b8d-8ae2-969f7fbd7801","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:43:14.928Z","parentId":"b073a95a-5772-43f8-8076-63a454c538fb"}
